"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The code does not correctly use Matplotlib because it does not clear the figure between iterations of the loop. This can lead to overlapping plots from different files. The plt.close() command at the end of the loop is not sufficient to clear the figure; plt.clf() should be used to clear the current figure before starting a new plot.\",\n  \"patch\": \"18a19\\n> plt.clf()\"\n}"